The paper deals with privacy-preserving planning in a multi-agent setting, which involves coordination through message passing. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of privacy leakage, which could fall under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the performance of the agents, which could relate to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Machine Learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the likely categories are cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.CR, cs.DC, and cs.LG, ordered from most to least likely.
